{
  "texts": [
    "In general, the classification of nilpotent Lie algebras admitting nilsoliton inner products is wide open as far as we know.While these metrics do not exist on any nilpotent Lie group, when they do, they are unique up to isometry, in a very strong sense: given any two nilsolitons h 1, h 2 on the same Lie group N, up to scaling there exists φ ∈ Aut(N) such that h 2 = φ * h 1 [Lau01].A left-invariant metric on a connected Lie group N is determined by an inner product h ∈ Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) on the Lie algebra 𝔫.",
    "The space of inner products is a Riemannian symmetric space of non-positive curvature: Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) = GL + (𝔫)/SO(𝔫, h).",
    "Here h is certain fixed inner product, and the action of GL + (𝔫) is by pull-back:(38) (q • h)(•, •) = h(q -1 •, q -1 •), q ∈ GL + (𝔫).The symmetric metric on Sym2 + (𝔫 *) is given for h ∈ Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) and k ∈ T h Sym 2 + (𝔫 *) = Sym 2 (𝔫 *) by (39) (g sym) h (k, k) = dim 𝔫 i,j=1k(e i, e j)k(e i, e j), for any h-orthonormal basis {e i } of 𝔫.",
    "See [Heb98, §3.1] for further details.",
    "In terms of this structure, if h is itself a nilsoliton with cosmological constant λ, then by the abovementioned uniqueness, the set of nilsoliton inner products on 𝔫 with cosmological constant λ is the orbit Aut(𝔫) • h ⊂ GL + (𝔫)/ SO(𝔫, h)."
  ]
}